commit_message:
Properly handle zero width characters (#89)

Feed data to Pyte one character at a time so that
Pyte ignoring data after a zero-width character
isn't a problem.

While we're at it, replace pyte.ByteStream by
pyte.Stream to simplify the code

Improve CI/CD pipeline

All artifacts are now built by the CI/CD pipeline.
When a commit is tagged, the following happens:
    - The Python package is built and uploaded
    to pypi.org or test.pypi.org
    - The manual pages are converted from Markdown
    to roff and added to the GitHub release corresponding
    to the tag
    - The GitHub pages website is built and uploaded to
    the gh-pages or gh-pages-staging branch of the
    GitHub repository

All of this makes the difference between sources and build artifacts
clearer and helps streamline the deployment process

Minor fixes for version 0.8.0

Update changelog
Fix deployment of man pages
Fix typos
Remove unused CLI options for record subcommand
Add stil frames to list of features
Abandon line events in favor of complete frames
